-- Sesa Goa Plans to Invest $6.7 Billion in Steel Plants, Press Trust Reports
-- B y   T h o m a s   A b r a h a m
-- 2010-10-24T06:07:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-24/sesa-goa-plans-to-invest-6-7-billion-in-steel-plants-press-trust-reports.html
Sesa Goa Ltd., the Indian unit of
Vedanta Resources Plc, plans to invest more than 300 billion
rupees ($6.7 billion) to make steel in Orissa and Jharkhand
states, the Press Trust of India reported, citing Managing
Director P.K. Mukherjee. Sesa plans to find a foreign company to
jointly run the steel projects, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
